  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\n\r\nWhen a peer disconnects, right now, subscribers to messages wait for a timeout before they realize that the peer is gone. This slows down syncing and other things (and in pathological cases with no timeout, can pause forever).\r\n\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\n~Maybe cause all subscribers to the peer to receive a TimeoutError immediately on peer disconnect.~\r\n\r\nImplement `deregister_peer` in `ResponseCandidateStream` and immediately `raise TimeoutError` on any pending requests.",
